{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888935086,"sessionID":"ses_284c71b07ffeI33an410PJA2WH","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3aa896001d6f2QM14UyE553","messageID":"msg_d7b395923001YtTORfZWPDIvvE","sessionID":"ses_284c71b07ffeI33an410PJA2WH","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-9f5a16fe7522419f977713298c4e87b7","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-034 |\n| Module | .github |\n| Language | YAML |\n| Size | L |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nEstablish a comprehensive CI/CD pipeline using GitHub Actions for the AgentCube project, automating build verification, code quality checks, testing, and release workflows. This proposal implements 12 workflows covering:\n\n1. **Build Verification**: Docker image builds on pull requests\n2. **Code Quality**: Go lint, Python lint (Ruff), spelling checks (codespell), copyright headers\n3. **Testing**: Unit tests with coverage, E2E tests on Kind, Python SDK tests\n4. **Code Generation**: Validation of generated artifacts\n5. **Release**: Multi-architecture image publication to GitHub Container Registry\n6. **Workflow Management**: Auto-approval for trusted contributors\n\n**Workflow Summary**:\n\n| Workflow | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `main.yml` | Docker build verification on PRs |\n| `e2e.yml` | End-to-end tests on Kind cluster |\n| `lint.yml` | Go linting (golangci-lint) |\n| `python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK unit tests |\n| `python-lint.yml` | Python linting (Ruff) |\n| `test-coverage.yml` | Go test coverage reporting |\n| `codegen-check.yml` | Generated code validation |\n| `copyright-check.yml` | Copyright header consistency |\n| `codespell.yml` | Spelling verification |\n| `build-push-release.yml` | Image publication on main/tags |\n| `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify plugin packaging and publishing |\n| `workflows-approve.yml` | Auto-approve trusted contributor runs |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Scope (范围)\n\n### 2.1 In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `.github/workflows/main.yml` | Pull request Docker build verification |\n| `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` | Kind-based E2E testing workflow |\n| `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | Go linting with path filtering |\n| `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK pytest execution |\n| `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` | Ruff-based Python linting |\n| `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` | Go test coverage with Codecov integration |\n| `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` | Generated code drift detection |\n| `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` | Copyright header validation |\n| `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` | Repository-wide spelling check |\n| `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` | Multi-arch image push to ghcr.io |\n| `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify plugin release automation |\n| `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` | First-time contributor workflow approval |\n\n### 2.2 Workflow Trigger Matrix\n\n| Workflow | Triggers | Branches | Path Filters |\n|----------|----------|----------|--------------|\n| `main.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | None |\n| `e2e.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | None |\n| `lint.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml` |\n| `python-sdk-tests.yml` | `pull_request`, `merge_group` | — | `sdk-python/**` |\n| `python-lint.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py` |\n| `test-coverage.yml` | `pull_request`, `merge_group`, `workflow_call` | — | All minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png` |\n| `codegen-check.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile` |\n| `copyright-check.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | All minus `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**` |\n| `codespell.yml` | `pull_request` | `main`, `release-*` | None |\n| `build-push-release.yml` | `push` | `main`, tags `v*.*.*` | None |\n| `dify-plugin-publish.yml` | `push` tags | `dify-plugin/v*` | None |\n| `workflows-approve.yml` | `pull_request_target` | `main`, `release-**` | None |\n\n### 2.3 Out of Scope\n\n| Item | Reason |\n|------|--------|\n| GitHub self-hosted runners | Using GitHub-hosted runners (ubuntu-latest) |\n| Custom CI infrastructure | Standard GitHub Actions suffices |\n| Third-party CI systems (Jenkins, GitLab CI) | GitHub-native solution preferred |\n| Deployment workflows | Deployment handled by Helm in clusters |\n| Security scanning (SAST/DAST) | Future AR for security tooling |\n| Performance benchmarks | Not in initial CI scope |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n\n### 3.1 新增文件\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `.github/workflows/main.yml` | Docker build workflow |\n| `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` | E2E test workflow |\n| `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | Go lint workflow |\n| `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK test workflow |\n| `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` | Python lint workflow |\n| `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` | Coverage workflow |\n| `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` | Codegen check workflow |\n| `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` | Copyright check workflow |\n| `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` | Spelling check workflow |\n| `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` | Release build workflow |\n| `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify plugin publish workflow |\n| `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` | Workflow approval workflow |\n\n### 3.2 修改文件\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| None | All workflows are new additions |\n\n### 3.3 Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `actions/checkout@v4` | Repository checkout |\n| `actions/setup-go@v5` | Go toolchain installation |\n| `actions/setup-python@v5` | Python toolchain installation |\n| `docker/setup-buildx-action@v3` | Docker Buildx setup |\n| `docker/login-action@v3` | Container registry authentication |\n| `docker/build-push-action@v5` | Multi-arch image builds |\n| `helm/kind-action@v1` | Kind cluster setup |\n| `dorny/paths-filter@v3` | Path-based workflow filtering |\n| `codecov/codecov-action@v4` | Coverage upload |\n| `github-script` | GitHub API operations |\n\n### 3.4 Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| Pull Request authors | Automatic validation on PRs |\n| Maintainers | Quality gate enforcement |\n| Release process | Automated image publishing on tags |\n| Dify plugin users | Plugin availability via dify-plugins repo |\n| First-time contributors | Streamlined workflow approval |\n\n### 3.5 Makefile Targets Required\n\n| Target | Workflow | Description |\n|--------|----------|-------------|\n| `docker-build` | `main.yml`, `e2e.yml` | Build workload manager image |\n| `docker-build-router` | `e2e.yml` | Build router image |\n| `docker-build-picod` | `e2e.yml` | Build picod image |\n| `docker-buildx-push` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push workload manager image |\n| `docker-buildx-push-router` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push router image |\n| `docker-buildx-push-picod` | `build-push-release.yml` | Push picod image |\n| `e2e` | `e2e.yml` | Run E2E test script |\n| `e2e-clean` | `e2e.yml` | Cleanup E2E resources |\n| `lint` | `lint.yml` | Run golangci-lint |\n| `gen-check` | `codegen-check.yml` | Verify generated code |\n| `gen-copyright` | `copyright-check.yml` | Generate copyright headers |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n\n### Alternative 1: Single Monolithic Workflow\n\n**Approach**: Combine all CI steps into a single workflow file.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Simpler structure, single file to maintain |\n| Cons | No parallel execution, longer feedback loop, all-or-nothing failure, no selective triggering |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Multiple workflows enable parallel execution, faster feedback, and path-based selective triggering. Critical checks (lint, build) complete faster than longer checks (E2E).\n\n### Alternative 2: GitLab CI / Jenkins\n\n**Approach**: Use alternative CI/CD platforms.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Potential for self-hosted infrastructure, different feature sets |\n| Cons | GitHub is the canonical repository; external CI adds complexity; no native GitHub integration |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. GitHub Actions provides native integration with the repository, requires no external infrastructure, and uses the same platform as the code hosting.\n\n### Alternative 3: Composite Actions for Reused Steps\n\n**Approach**: Extract common steps (setup, checkout) into composite actions.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | DRY principle, centralized maintenance |\n| Cons | Additional complexity for minimal code; current duplication is acceptable for clarity |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected for initial implementation. May reconsider if step duplication becomes unmanageable. Current workflow count (12) is manageable.\n\n### Alternative 4: Dependabot for Action Versioning\n\n**Approach**: Use Dependabot to auto-update action versions.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Automatic security updates, version tracking |\n| Cons | Adds dependency management overhead; pinning to major versions is sufficient |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected for now. Pinning to major versions (v3, v4, v5) provides stability while allowing minor updates. Can add Dependabot configuration in a future AR.\n\n### Alternative 5: Reusable Workflows for Coverage\n\n**Approach**: Extract test-coverage.yml as a reusable workflow callable from other workflows.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Reusability across multiple calling workflows |\n| Cons | Only test-coverage.yml uses `workflow_call`; no other callers exist |\n\n**Decision**: Partially adopted. `test-coverage.yml` already uses `workflow_call` for future reusability, but this is not the primary pattern for other workflows.\n\n### Alternative 6: Self-Hosted Runners for E2E\n\n**Approach**: Use self-hosted runners with pre-configured Kind clusters for faster E2E.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Faster E2E execution, persistent Kind clusters |\n| Cons | Infrastructure overhead, security considerations, maintenance burden |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. GitHub-hosted runners provide consistent, isolated environments with zero maintenance overhead. E2E execution time is acceptable (~10-15 minutes).\n\n### Alternative 7: Merge Queue with Branch Protection\n\n**Approach**: Use GitHub merge queues instead of PR-based checks.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Ensures linear history, serialized merges |\n| Cons | Additional configuration, not needed for current team size |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected for now. `merge_group` trigger is supported in `test-coverage.yml` and `python-sdk-tests.yml` for future merge queue adoption. Current PR-based workflow is sufficient.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Action version deprecation | Pin to major versions; monitor deprecation notices |\n| Rate limiting on GitHub Actions | Path filtering reduces unnecessary runs; workflow approval for first-time contributors |\n| E2E flakiness | Kind cluster isolation; artifact collection on failure; cleanup in `always()` block |\n| Registry credentials exposure | Use `GITHUB_TOKEN` (built-in) for ghcr.io; no long-lived secrets |\n| Coverage report size | Only cover `./pkg/...`; upload as artifact for large reports |\n| False positives in codespell | Temporary file removal for known false positives; ignore list for common issues |\n| Buildx cache growth | Use GitHub Actions cache; prune old caches periodically |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Create `.github/workflows/` directory structure\n- [ ] Implement `main.yml` with Docker build verification\n- [ ] Implement `e2e.yml` with Kind cluster and test execution\n- [ ] Implement `lint.yml` with path filtering for Go files\n- [ ] Implement `python-sdk-tests.yml` with pytest execution\n- [ ] Implement `python-lint.yml` with Ruff configuration\n- [ ] Implement `test-coverage.yml` with Codecov integration\n- [ ] Implement `codegen-check.yml` with `make gen-check`\n- [ ] Implement `copyright-check.yml` with `make gen-copyright`\n- [ ] Implement `codespell.yml` with ignore list configuration\n- [ ] Implement `build-push-release.yml` with multi-arch builds\n- [ ] Implement `dify-plugin-publish.yml` with cross-repo PR creation\n- [ ] Implement `workflows-approve.yml` with contributor check\n- [ ] Add required secrets to repository settings (`CODECOV_TOKEN` optional, `PLUGIN_ACTION` for dify)\n- [ ] Configure branch protection rules requiring status checks\n- [ ] Test each workflow with sample PRs\n\n---\n\n## 7. References\n\n- GitHub Actions Documentation: https://docs.github.com/en/actions\n- Docker Buildx Documentation: https://docs.docker.com/buildx/working-with-buildx/\n- Kind Documentation: https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/\n- golangci-lint: https://golangci-lint.run/\n- Ruff: https://docs.astral.sh/ruff/\n- Codecov: https://docs.codecov.com/\n- ci-cd/spec.md — CI/CD requirements specification\n- ci-cd/design.md — CI/CD design documentation\n- test/e2e/run_e2e.sh — E2E test execution script\n- Makefile — Build and test targets","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-034/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775888935078,"end":1775888935084}}}}
